relate-agent

DESCRIPTION
  A agent is a container of DBMSs, it takes care of file system and access to
  the DBMS. Aura and Desktop are agents, and in the case of single DBMS
  instances either locally or remotely, the host is the agent.

USAGE
  relate agent add <name> <path|url>
  relate agent update <name|id>
  relate agent remove <name|id>
  relate agent list [--format=<format>|--ids]
  relate agent use <name|id>
  relate agent current [--format=<format>]

OPTIONS
  --format=<format>       Specify what information should be returned.
  --ids                   Return only IDs.
  --file=<path>           File to load context from.

NOTES
  add:
    If no <path|url> is specified, it should be possible to pass the configuration
    file for the agent through STDIN.
  update:
    Opens the configuration file on the default editor.
